docs.snippet: GENEVA, June 30 Fortysix nations today signed the documents putting into effect the biggest round of trade liberalization in history, the Kennedy round.
docs.lead_paragraph: GENEVA, June 30 Fortysix nations today signed the documents putting into effect the biggest round of trade liberalization in history, the Kennedy round.
docs.abstract: 46 nations sign final act of Kennedy round, Geneva, putting tariff cuts into effect; 38 nations making tariff concessions, 8 developing countries (Ceylon, Greece, Indonesia, Nicaragua, Nigeria, Pakistan, Sierra Leone, Uruguay) making no concessions yet; 8 other nations that took part in discussions but not in fianl talks do not sign; signatories listed, various accords noted; cuts affect 70% of industrial countries' dutiable imports, 2/3 of them 50% or more, 1/5 of them 25-50%; chief categories of affected items noted; developing countries voice disappointment over round, hold they do not share in benefits to same extent as developed nations; GATT chief E Wyndham White warns protectionism must still be overcome and trade liberalization tested by periods of econ stress; reproves US and EEC for restrictions in certain phases of round; W M Blumenthal signs for US, reads wire from Pres Johnson hailing accord
